result.execSummary:
The defendant Hunter Reed Rousseau was found guilty of the following charge(s) in this case. One or more other charges in this case were dismissed. The dismissed charges were not proven and have no legal effect. Hunter Reed Rousseau is presumed innocent of the dismissed charges.

  • Hunter Reed Rousseau was found guilty of Possession of THC, an unclassified misdemeanor, Wisconsin Statutes 961.41(3g)(e).

Notice to employers: It may be a violation of state law to discriminate against a job applicant because of an arrest or conviction record. For more information, see Wisconsin Statute 111.335 and the Department of Workforce Development's publication, Arrest and Conviction Records under the Law.

Defendant Hunter Reed Rousseau in court.  Chad A. Hendee appeared for the State of Wisconsin.
Atty Hendee states that the defendant was supposed to appear yesterday and a warrant was authorized.

BY THE COURT:  Based on the defendant's appearance today; the warrant is quashed.

Court questions the defendant as to why he did not appear.Defendant read the date incorrectly.
Atty Hendee states that an offer was provided.  Defendant would like to accept the offer. 
BY THE COURT: Court will recess so the defendant can fill out paperwork.

BACK ON THE RECORD:

  Court advises defendant of right to an attorney.  Defendant waives their right to an attorney.    Court finds waiver made knowingly, voluntarily & Intelligently.
Defendant enters a Guilty plea
  Court questions defendant regarding plea. Advises of Constitutional Rights and elements of the charge.  Court finds plea made knowingly, voluntarily & Intelligently.  Court relies on the criminal complaint for a factual basis.  

BY THE COURT:  Court finds a sufficient factual basis to support the charges.  Court accepts defendant's plea and finds defendant guilty of Ct. 1.  Ct. 2 to be dismissed.

BY THE COURT:  Pay fine and costs = $442.00
